Function Maps

EMM Toolkit 2.0

Overview

For continued support of Zebra Android device administration, EMM solution providers must adapt their server and agent apps to the standards-based approaches being implemented in Android Enterprise APIs and Managed Configurations.

The tables on this page map the functions of the Zebra MX Management System (MXMS) to Android Enterprise API functions (immediately below), and to Managed Configurations, which are used when no AE API is implemented. Managed Configuration parameters are configured through the Zebra OEMConfig app on the device. Both approaches use public specifications developed by Google and the Android community.

Information subject to change without notice.

MX-to-AE APIs

The table below maps the functions of the Zebra MX Managament System (MXMS) to Android Enterprise API functions. Use this table to determine whether MX functions currently supported by an EMM solution are implemented in the Android Enterprise APIs and therefore map directly.

If no API exists, standards-based implementation is possible through Zebra OEMConfig. Its mappings appear on the MX-to-OEMConfig table that follows.

Wi-Fi

UseProxy=1:”Manual”

ProxyHostName

ProxyPort

BypassProxy

5.0

try

{

  Class proxySettings = Class.forName("android.net.IpConfiguration$ProxySettings");

  Class[] setProxyParams = new Class[2];

  setProxyParams[0] = proxySettings;

  setProxyParams[1] = ProxyInfo.class;

  Method setProxy = config.getClass().getDeclaredMethod("setProxy", setProxyParams);

  setProxy.setAccessible(true);

  List<String> exclList = new ArrayList<String>();

 

  if (null != byPassProxy)

  {

      String proxy[] = byPassProxy.split(",");

      for (int i = 0; i < proxy.length; ++i)

      {

          exclList.add(proxy[i]);

      }

  }

 

  ProxyInfo desiredProxy = ProxyInfo.buildDirectProxy(proxyHostName ,proxyPort, exclList);

  Object[] methodParams = new Object[2];

  methodParams[0] = Enum.valueOf(proxySettings,”STATIC");

  methodParams[1] = desiredProxy;

  setProxy.invoke(config, methodParams);

}

catch (Exception e)

{

  e.printStackTrace();

}

UseProxy=3:”Proxy Auto-Config”

ProxyPAC

5.0

try

{

  Class proxySettings = Class.forName("android.net.IpConfiguration$ProxySettings");

  Class[] setProxyParams = new Class[2];

  setProxyParams[0] = proxySettings;

  setProxyParams[1] = ProxyInfo.class;

  Method setProxy = config.getClass().getDeclaredMethod("setProxy",   setProxyParams);

  setProxy.setAccessible(true);

  Uri mPacFileUrl = Uri.parse(pac);

  ProxyInfo desiredProxy = ProxyInfo.buildPacProxy(mPacFileUrl);

  Object[] methodParams = new Object[2];

  methodParams[0] = Enum.valueOf(proxySettings,”PAC");

  methodParams[1] = desiredProxy;

  setProxy.invoke(config, methodParams);

  }

  catch (Exception e)

    e.printStackTrace();
